derivation.yuyuan_name: late 16th cent. (in the sense 'impossible to imagine'): from French, or from late Latin inconsiderabilis, from in- 'not' + considerabilis 'worthy of consideration' (see considerable)

entry.tran: 不值得考虑的;小的;无足轻重的
entry.def: If you describe an amount or quality as not inconsiderable, you are emphasizing that it is, in fact, large or present to a large degree.
